External Knowledge: 
Mask Mandate refers to a public health measure that requires people to wear masks in public places to slow the spread of a disease, such as COVID-19; 
A person is considered to be between the ages of 60 and 79 if their age falls within this range, inclusive.

sql:
SELECT measure_name
FROM public_health_measures
WHERE start_date <= '2020-12-31' AND end_date >= '2020-01-01';

SELECT age_group_id, metric_id, value
FROM metric_values
WHERE week_id = 1 AND age_group_id = 1;
